  "text": "Multivariate Imputation by Chained Equations (MICE, see [CITATION_1] for an overview) is then applied to address the missing data. MICE is deemed as the proper multiple imputation method as it is specified on a variable-by-variable basis. The uncertainty of the amount of missing values and the actual result set make it hard to predict if the multivariate distribution describes the data, such as is required by Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) implementations of multiple imputations. MICE overcomes this problem (van Buuren and Groothuis-oudshoorn 2011) . The round of imputations will be selected following the method described by [CITATION_2] . This results in a complete, imputed dataset.",
